records.addlTxt: Case called at 9:20 AM.  Defendant Kethan Alan Rood in court, in custody, with attorney Guy Taylor Jenna L Gill appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Taylor informs the court Defendant was detained on cash bond condition for failure to appear and have stipulated to revocation of Deferred Agreement.  State informs the Court Defendant has served 2 days.  Court will revoke deferred judgment agreement with 2 days sentence credit.  State requesting warrant be quashed, 60 days to pay/$243.00 + costs.  Court will order.  Court will release Defendant from jail, vacating warrant.
bond may be posted in the amount of $400.00.  If defendant posts defendant shall appear the following Monday at 9:00 am

Case called at 2:28 PM.

Attorney Bucher informs the court this matter is resolved and files waiver form with the court.
Defendant withdraws plea of "NOT GUILTY" and enters a plea of "NO CONTEST".
Court questions defendant re: plea and waiver of rights.
Court questions attorney Bucher re: her clients plea and waiver of rights.
That there is a factual basis.
Court finds plea and waiver is made freely, knowingly & intelligently.

Attorney Bucher concurs with the state.
Court grants motion of the parties and orders defendant be placed on a DP for a period of 12 months with conditions.
